Anh - Anh
cornu
['kɔ:nju:]
■ noun (plural cornua-njʊə) Anatomy
1》 a horn-shaped projection of the thyroid cartilage or of certain bones.
2》 either of the two lateral cavities of the womb, into which the Fallopian tubes pass.
3》 each of three elongated parts of the lateral ventricles of the brain.
Derivatives
cornualadjective
Origin
C17: from L., 'horn'.

Từ điển Kỹ thuật (EN)
Lĩnh vực: y học
